<br>
1.  Guild decides to help all its members gain their epics.<br>
<br>
2.  Player A gets his epic due to the work of the rest of the guild.<br>
<br>
3.  Player A continues to help others in his guild get their epics, but begins to get bored after a couple of months of just epic encounters and begins to crave bigger and better fights.<br>
<br>
4.  Player A leaves the guild to join one that is doing bigger and better things.<br>
<br>
5.  Soon the guild needs to begin recruiting new people due to the exodus of players that have gotten their epics.  New people need epics, so the cycle continues.<br>
<br>
I'd say that the key for a guild that may be in this situation is to mix things up a bit, don't focus completely on obtaining epics, but do a mix of other raids.  That way you can keep those who have their epics happy and feeling that they aren't just spinning their wheels.<br>
